                     <interp inst="t18270405-89-defend608" type="age" value="14"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was indicted for <rs id="t18270405-89-off502" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270405-89-off502" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-89-off502" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18270405-89-cd503" type="crimeDate">15th of January</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-89-off502 t18270405-89-cd503"></join>, 1 waistcoat-piece, value 7s.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               <persName id="t18270405-89-victim609" type="victimName">
                  Edward 
                  Riley
               <interp inst="t18270405-89-victim609" type="surname" value="Riley"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-89-victim609" type="given" value="Edward"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-89-victim609" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-89-off502 t18270405-89-victim609"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>EDWARD RILEY. I am a <rs id="t18270405-89-viclabel504" type="occupation">tailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-89-victim609 t18270405-89-viclabel504"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18270405-89-crimeloc505">Ratcliff-highway</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270405-89-crimeloc505" type="placeName" value="Ratcliff-highway"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270405-89-crimeloc505" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-89-off502 t18270405-89-crimeloc505"></join>. On the 15th of January, between five and six o'clock in the evening, I was in my shop - I saw the prisoner come and take a piece of waistcoat toilenet through a hole in the window - I saw his person perfectly - it had been close to the place - I went out, and took him with it about two or three doors off - he was walking.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270405-89-person610">
                  CHARLES 
                  ROBINSON
               <interp inst="t18270405-89-person610" type="surname" value="ROBINSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-89-person610" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-89-person610" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I was sent for, and took the prisoner with this waistcoat-piece sticking in his bosom - he said he had found it.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. Some person threw it down by me, and I took it up.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 14.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18270405-89-verdict506" type="verdictDescription">
